1
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:23,400
I'm sorry if I just visited you
now.

2
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:26,500
You know that when I come home
here in Sorsogon,

3
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:28,167
all I remember

4
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:31,867
are the bad things
that happened to our family.

5
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:33,767
I love someone else.

6
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,100
It's Adora.

7
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:36,400
She's already pregnant.

8
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:38,367
How about our daughter?

9
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,633
How about Celeste?

10
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:45,800
Mother, you haven't eaten
since this morning.

11
00:00:45,867 --> 00:00:48,467
Mother, you will get sick.

12
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:48,767
Mother.

13
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:51,900
Mother?

14
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:53,533
Mother?

15
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:55,167
Mother, wake up.

16
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:58,967
Mother. Mother, let's eat.

17
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:01,567
Mother, no, no, no.

18
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:03,600
Mother, this isn't it, right?
Mother!

19
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,700
Mother, no, no...

20
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:06,267
Mother.

21
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:10,400
I'm really trying my best
to forgive.

22
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:12,233
I'm trying, Mother.

23
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,367
You are my only family.

24
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:19,733
I miss you, Mother.

25
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:26,000
Miss, would you like to buy some
handicrafts from Sorsogon?

26
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:26,967
Please buy.

27
00:01:28,267 --> 00:01:31,900
Celeste!

28
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:33,433
I'm sorry.

29
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:34,767
I was also busy in Manila

30
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,567
that's why we weren't able
to talk.

31
00:01:36,633 --> 00:01:37,900
Liar of the year.

32
00:01:37,967 --> 00:01:39,067
What "I'm busy"
are you talking about?

33
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:41,533
Cuz, let's talk first.

34
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:42,767
Hurry, come on.

35
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:44,233
Did you notice?
A lot of things have changed

36
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:46,667
here in Sorsogon
since you lived in Manila.

37
00:01:46,733 --> 00:01:48,233
But this is the first time
I found out

38
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:50,067
that you like guys
with almond-shaped eyes.

39
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,467
Just like you, you also have
almond-shaped eyes.

40
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:53,500
You look good together,
in fairness.

41
00:01:53,567 --> 00:01:56,500
But his looks are very different
from that of Mikoy's.

42
00:01:56,567 --> 00:01:58,733
But a lot has changed
with your ex.

43
00:01:58,800 --> 00:01:59,433
I don't know about him.

44
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:01,500
Who's brave here?

45
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:05,800
Come out who is brave!

46
00:02:08,067 --> 00:02:10,100
I think Mikoy got depressed
when you broke up.

47
00:02:10,167 --> 00:02:11,267
It was your fault, Cuz.

48
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:13,267
Why did you and Mikoy
suddenly break up?

49
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:18,367
Actually,
I can't remember anymore.

50
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:19,967
That was a long time ago.

51
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:22,567
Wait, just in time.
There is Mikoy.

52
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:23,733
Mikoy!

53
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:37,933
Thank you for bringing my wife
here.

54
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,467
You're welcome. Take care.

55
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:44,400
Mikoy!

56
00:03:44,467 --> 00:03:45,067
Mikoy!

57
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,100
Celeste?

58
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,200
I really have to go.

59
00:04:13,433 --> 00:04:15,167
Why, Cuz? Cuz, wait.

60
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:16,500
Just wait.

61
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,067
The ice cream
is not yet paid for.

62
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:20,567
Just a moment, I'll be back.

63
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:20,933
Just a moment.

64
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:24,933
Hey Cuz, wait.

65
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,967
Just a second.

66
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:27,300
What's with you?
You just saw Mikoy

67
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,767
and you're acting like that.

68
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:31,600
Didn't I tell you
that I have to leave?

69
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:33,300
But in fairness,
he's still handsome.

70
00:04:33,367 --> 00:04:35,700
- He's still really yummy!
- Not really.

71
00:04:35,767 --> 00:04:36,933
Hey, in case you have forgotten,

72
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,333
you fell in love with him
before.

73
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,400
- That was before.
- Admit it.

74
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:40,667
That was before not now.

75
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:41,500
Liar!

76
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,300
Celeste.

77
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,400
You have the nerve to smile.

78
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:56,433
Wait.

79
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,200
Celeste. I just want to ask
how you are.

80
00:06:01,467 --> 00:06:01,800
Hi.

81
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:03,900
How are you?

82
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,500
I'm okay. How about you?

83
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,100
I'm good.
I've never been better.

84
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:13,067
Good, good.

85
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:16,700
You are a very successful
fashion designer now.

86
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:17,633
I'm glad.

87
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:20,067
It's funny?

88
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:22,567
I'm glad.

89
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:23,900
Oh, sorry.

90
00:06:23,967 --> 00:06:26,533
- It's because there are waves.
- Yeah.

91
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,067
You...

92
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:31,633
You look good.

93
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:35,367
I mean, you look very successful
also.

94
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:36,333
Thank you.
You, too.

95
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:40,233
Are you engaged?

96
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:44,233
Yes, actually.

97
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,133
It's beautiful, isn't it?

98
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:46,733
It's okay.

99
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:48,800
When is the wedding?

100
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:52,300
Soon, very soon.

101
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,367
Am I invited?

102
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,933
Of course, yes.

103
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:58,533
Of course.

104
00:07:01,433 --> 00:07:04,867
Anyway, what keeps you busy
these days?

105
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:11,167
Nothing much, I'm busy
with Grandmother Ikay's canteen.

106
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:13,067
- There are 7 branches.
- Nice. Wow.

107
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:16,033
I also do a lot of voluntary
work.

108
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:18,533
I manage the sunflower farm.

109
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,667
I'm also a part-time librarian.

110
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:22,767
Wow, sounds exciting.

111
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:27,567
Yes, it's exciting because
I'm happy with what I'm doing.

112
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:28,000
How about you?

113
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:30,367
Sorry, what?

114
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:32,767
Are you asking me if I'm happy?

115
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,433
Yes, of course, super.

116
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,867
I'm super happy.

117
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:39,067
I mean, the best times
of my life.

118
00:07:39,133 --> 00:07:41,333
I've never been this happy ever,
actually.

119
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:42,833
Good.

120
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,533
I'm happy if you're happy.

121
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,600
Okay, well...

122
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,867
I'm sorry I have to go.

123
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:57,500
Because you know, I need
to go back to Manila.

124
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:59,233
And I still have to do
a lot of things.

125
00:07:59,300 --> 00:07:59,867
So, is it okay?

126
00:08:01,533 --> 00:08:01,733
Okay.

127
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:07,667
Okay? I mean, is it okay
if I leave?

128
00:08:07,733 --> 00:08:07,967
Yeah.

129
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,233
Okay. Okay...

130
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:15,267
well you take care.
I'm happy to see you.

131
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:18,633
I'm also happy to see you.

132
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:23,167
Okay, cheerios.

133
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:24,800
Bye.

134
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:39,600
Oh God, that was awkward.
What's that?

135
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:41,333
Why would he look like that?

136
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:42,467
And his smile...

137
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:45,267
what's that?

138
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,033
Oh my gosh!

139
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:47,967
Irritating.

140
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,033
I look awful, my God.

141
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:03,100
I'm also happy to see you, wow.

142
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,567
My God, what kind of delivery
is that?

143
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:07,467
You don't know if it's genuine
or sarcastic.

144
00:09:07,533 --> 00:09:08,700
Is he really happy to see me?

145
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,233
Such trivial matters.

146
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:15,600
I look awful, haggard.

147
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:18,133
How I wish we didn't see
each other.

148
00:09:22,067 --> 00:09:22,733
Aircon!

149
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,233
Mikoy!

150
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:35,400
Mikoy.

151
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:35,967
You're fast.

152
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,300
- Mikoy.
- Hey.

153
00:09:38,367 --> 00:09:39,533
How are you?

154
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,267
- I'm okay.
- What did you and Cuz Celeste

155
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,400
talk about earlier?

156
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:44,033
Tell me.

157
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:46,933
Nothing, we just asked
how each other is doing.

158
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:48,600
Is that so?

159
00:09:50,267 --> 00:09:52,633
Was there any spark?

160
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:54,967
Nothing.

161
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:58,867
There's no pinch?

162
00:09:58,933 --> 00:10:00,300
The truth, admit it.

163
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:02,867
Admit it.

164
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:04,867
Nothing, what's with you?
Celeste is getting married.

165
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:07,733
You know we have been separated
for a long time.

166
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:08,833
She moved on already.

167
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,500
I also moved on.

168
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:12,567
You have moved on?

169
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,633
You're the liar of the year.

170
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,167
You're driving me crazy.

171
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:16,867
Stop it.

172
00:10:18,467 --> 00:10:19,267
You should clean my car.

173
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:23,267
Wait, where's the rag?

174
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:24,767
- Wait.
- Look for one here.

175
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:28,533
Wait. I have no rag.

176
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,033
Seriously?

177
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,367
Seriously!

178
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,700
No, oh my...

179
00:11:22,967 --> 00:11:24,533
Jamaica!

180
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,167
What's this car
you got me?

181
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:30,267
I said vintage,
not something that conks out.

182
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,133
It's driving me crazy!
What will I do now?

183
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,400
Nobody's here.
I'm in the middle of nowhere.

184
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:37,633
I already scolded my contact
in the car rental services.

185
00:11:38,933 --> 00:11:42,100
Just wait for my contact
who will help you there.

186
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,233
Haggard!

187
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:45,733
Hurry up.

188
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:51,967
One more time.

189
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:54,733
What's this?

190
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:57,867
What's this?

191
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:58,767
What's this?

192
00:12:01,267 --> 00:12:04,033
Did you cook all of that?

193
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,667
Yes, just me.

194
00:12:05,733 --> 00:12:08,500
Some of the dishes
that grandmother cooked earlier,

195
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:11,433
I've already delivered them
to the canteen.

196
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:16,567
Your wife-to-be is very lucky,
Mikoy.

197
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:19,600
You're very hardworking
and handsome.

198
00:12:19,667 --> 00:12:22,000
You don't run out of talent.

199
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:23,300
Do you want us to be a couple?

200
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:30,033
Don't get your hopes up.
Wake up!

201
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:32,033
I can only offer you friendship.

202
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,267
Whatever.

203
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:40,233
By the way, Mikoy, what else
can you not do?

204
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:42,633
Only one.

205
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:44,200
What?

206
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,667
That is to neglect my family
here in Sorsogon.

207
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:50,767
Like what Celeste did?

208
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:04,967
Hello, Mayor?

209
00:13:07,733 --> 00:13:10,100
Okay, no problem, I'm leaving.

210
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:17,133
You clean the house.

211
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:23,367
One more time, try.

212
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:25,600
Hey baby girl, let's try
one more time.

213
00:13:25,667 --> 00:13:28,600
Everybody deserves a second try,
a second chance.

214
00:13:28,667 --> 00:13:28,967
Let's try.

215
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:32,667
Let's try again.

216
00:13:38,033 --> 00:13:38,733
One more, come on.

217
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,133
There you go.

218
00:13:44,167 --> 00:13:46,567
AC, please come to me.

219
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:48,667
We are back in business.

220
00:13:48,733 --> 00:13:49,733
Thank you very much.

221
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:57,333
You will answer to me, Jamaica.

222
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,700
I'm telling you.

223
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:00,733
All right, it's okay. I'm happy.

224
00:14:19,667 --> 00:14:21,033
Your father must be proud
of you, Mikoy.

225
00:14:22,267 --> 00:14:24,933
You know,
when Dante was still alive,

226
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,367
it's his dream for you

227
00:14:26,433 --> 00:14:29,667
to become the Dean of College
of Education like him.

228
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,933
I'm not as intelligent
as my father.

229
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:36,133
I'm okay being
a part-time librarian

230
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:40,800
and a volunteer probation
officer of the city hall.

231
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,067
What's with you?

232
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:44,333
You should give it a try.

233
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,800
Remember, you're good.

234
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:50,400
By the way,
have you seen the tarp

235
00:14:50,467 --> 00:14:52,967
in the newly built
Galleon Replica Chapel

236
00:14:53,033 --> 00:14:54,000
in Sitio Guibalon?

237
00:14:55,133 --> 00:14:56,433
Not yet, Mayor.

238
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,000
You should see that because
you really look handsome there.

239
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:04,400
I asked them to put that there
so a lot of people will see it

240
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:09,133
because that's where the very
first mass in Luzon was held.

241
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,800
I'm sure it will become
a tourist attraction.

242
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:17,167
And when the local
and international tourists

243
00:15:17,233 --> 00:15:20,433
see our library promotion
advertising tarp,

244
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:23,667
I'm sure they'll also be enticed
to go there.

245
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,233
That's exciting, Mayor.

246
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,800
You should see it.

247
00:15:27,867 --> 00:15:29,600
But do I look handsome there?

248
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:32,367
You're far better than me
if you see it.

249
00:15:32,433 --> 00:15:34,333
You look handsome there.

250
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,433
I'll show that to grandmother.
She will be happy.

251
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:37,967
Wait, how is your grandmother?

252
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:41,233
She's still busy cooking.

253
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:42,500
I'll bring you food
one of these days.

254
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:44,000
I like her taro
with coconut milk

255
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:45,900
especially if it's spicy.

256
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:47,633
- Give my regards to her.
- Yes.

257
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,633
We haven't seen each other
in a long time

258
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:52,367
- since Dante died, okay?
- Yes.

259
00:15:52,433 --> 00:15:56,733
The truth is, your grandmother
is very close to my heart.

260
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,300
Don't court my grandmother.

261
00:15:58,367 --> 00:16:01,233
If only we could turn back time,

262
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,033
with the beauty
of your grandmother,
it's possible.

263
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:07,000
My grandmother is hot.
She is hotter than chili.

264
00:16:07,067 --> 00:16:08,233
Maybe her body is full of chili.

265
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:32,833
What's this?

266
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:37,267
What's with this day?

267
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:39,000
What is this?

268
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:40,367
Is this the end of the world?

269
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:41,267
Can you still handle it?

270
00:16:42,467 --> 00:16:44,100
Oh my God, my bags.

271
00:16:44,167 --> 00:16:44,700
Oh my God!

272
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,667
